title: Illusion of transparency
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The //illusion of transparency// is a tendency to overestimate the degree to which one's mental state is known and understood by others.

Similarly, the //observer's illusion of transparency// is a tendency to overestimate how well one understands others' personal mental states.